# Secrets
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
credentials.json

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak

# Local overrides (not shared)
settings.local.json
CLAUDE.local.md

# Third-party skills installed via uipro/marketplace (not our code)
.claude/skills/
# Git worktrees created during experiments (machine-local paths, not portable)
.claude/worktrees/
.coverage
coverage.json
.gitnexus
.claude/launch.json
# Runtime locks (created by scheduled task runner)
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Auto-generated per-machine state (written by SessionStart hooks)
# project_profile.md is machine/cwd-specific — regenerated each session by
# project_classifier.py. last_pattern_escalation.txt is the weekly-review timer.
.claude/memory/_auto/project_profile.md
# **/ prefix (not just root-anchored) because a hook subprocess sometimes
# inherits the caller's cwd instead of repo root, writing state under
# hooks/.claude/state/ instead of <repo>/.claude/state/ — same class of bug
# as cross_domain_insights.md "Hook/plugin subprocess inherits CALLER's cwd".
**/.claude/state/

# Agent runtime memory (memory:project scope, e.g. reviewer agent) — local
# scratch, not shipped config. No prior precedent for tracking this in repo.
.claude/agent-memory/

# Skill runtime data — NEVER commit
# WHY: skills like notebooklm create data/ (auth tokens, browser cookies,
# Google session state) and .venv/ (500MB playwright binaries) inside
# their own directory. If a user runs the skill from within this repo
# clone, these dirs appear and would be staged by `git add .`.
# Browser_state may contain Google account cookies — public commit = account hijack.
skills/extensions/*/data/
skills/extensions/*/.venv/
skills/extensions/*/scripts/__pycache__/
skills/core/*/data/
skills/core/*/.venv/
skills/core/*/scripts/__pycache__/

# Specific high-risk files (defence in depth — match even if patterns above change)
**/auth_info.json
**/browser_state/
**/state.json
**/sessions.json

# IDE-local (Cursor) — editor harness config, not part of the shipped config
.cursor/

# Internal session reports — not intended for public repo
# WHY these two joined the pattern 2026-07-24 (external audit + P0-B): the
# rule above already existed but only PREVENTS future commits -- it never
# retroactively untracks files committed before the rule was added.
# docs/CODEX_AUDIT_RESULTS.md and docs/CODEX_AUDIT_SPEC.md were the same class
# of one-off internal artifact (a past audit run + the spec that produced it,
# not a documented framework feature like null_results/ or activeContext.md)
# but had no pattern at all. All four were `git rm --cached` in the same
# commit that added this comment, closing the gap for real, not just in intent.
docs/SESSION_REPORT*.md
docs/GITHUB_SHOWCASE_AUDIT.md
docs/CODEX_AUDIT_RESULTS.md
docs/CODEX_AUDIT_SPEC.md

# graphify output
graphify-out/
